Talking about 3D effects... What about scaling and rotating sprites on the NES ? It would take a few pattern table space and a few code for each scanling/rotating sprite.<br />I think scanling isn't too hard. Using the trick to have 16-bit counter and une only the high 8 bits as the pixel index should work fine.<br />Rotating would be pretty undoable to what I currently know. Any ideas ?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Feb 17, 2006 12:36 pm</p><hr />
